cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV 

This paper deals with the mathematical formalization of invariances in learning algorithms, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the invariances of linear regression and ridge regression, which are commonly used in data science and statistics, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the application of the framework to computer vision, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category.
